CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1957, pg. 17, reads: "Slums Growing in Homewood? -Whine Gardens' - The Rev. Linwood Coleman was disturbed when he was informed that neighbors are complaining about the four dogs and five kennels, three of which are shown in backyard of the minister's home at 7415 Race St."
TitMainTitle: Fenced yard of Rev. Linwood Coleman, with dog and three dog houses, 7415 Race Street, Homewood
